.TH "inc_nlink" 9 "inc_nlink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
inc_nlink \- directly increment an inode's link count
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" inc_nlink
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a low-level filesystem helper to replace any
direct filesystem manipulation of i_nlink.  Currently,
it is only here for parity with \fBdec_nlink\fP.
